Canonical Doctrine

Daemons are personalities. Operators are procedures. Algorithms are atoms. Medusa is the genome that allows new intelligences to evolve without reinventing their cognitive machinery.

I think this is one of the more important architectural additions because it shifts Pantheon from a collection of named components into a true compositional cognitive operating system. Daemons become expressions of reusable algorithm families, and Medusa becomes the canonical registry that allows those families to be discovered, recombined, benchmarked, and promoted into the kernel over time.